Northrop Grumman Space Systems is seeking a GBSD Data Management Analyst. This position will be located in Roy, UT and will support the GBSD program. This role may offer a competitive relocation assistance package.
What you'll get to do:
Perform Data Management (DM) on state-of-the-art GBSD Systems.
Works with all levels of management, program IPT Leads, Program Managers, Chief Engineers, etc. to ensure products are generated, managed, reviewed and approved according to sector-approved processes.
Processing CDRLs, SDRLs and maintaining program documentation in accordance with GEIA Standard 859, industry/ISO/DoD standards and specifications tailored program needs.
Manages and provides schedules, status reports and metrics and interface with multiple disciplines on the GBSD program.
Supports the implementation of Configuration and Data Management (CDM) activities using our Product Data Management (PDM) tools such as SharePoint, JIRA and CPLM.
Supports the Government Customer as well as all levels of management and the IPT teams.
Ensuring program data has been approved, distributed and managed appropriately in accordance with sector and program approved processes.
Data Planning, Scheduling and Management requires the DM Analyst to have the skillset to utilize the DD Form 1423, Integrated Master Schedule (IMS) and the Statement of Work (SOW), scheduling and managing each deliverable based on the contractual delivery requirement.
Responsible for validating data and verifying that the data is consistent with existing procedures and guidelines, as well as security markings. Analysis and validation of project deliverables and non-deliverables, contract and non-contract data requirements, and customer-supplied data are to be performed.
Data Retention, utilizing approved controls for the delivery of program data.
Implements controls for safeguarding intellectual property.
Ensures completeness and eliminate duplication.
Issues controlled document numbers based on the applicable WBS identification.
Ensures the appropriate marking of data (e.g. proprietary data rights, classification).
Maintains the current and historical metadata regarding data status and customer disposition (approval/disapproval, etc.).
Establishes and document records, custodians, and project-unique records management requirements.
Publishes and make program documents available for the GBSD team.
Coordinates with IPTs on delivery schedules of CDRLs.
Receipt and processing of SDRLs.
Administers CDM configuration-controlled CDRL/SDRL information within the SharePoint and CPLM tools (must have knowledge and understanding of data management practices and procedures).
Assesses risk issues and develop resolutions to meet productivity, quality, and client-satisfaction goals and objectives.
Plans and coordinates release and control of program deliverables to ensure that contractual requirements are being met in a timely and efficient manner.

You’ll Bring These Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree and 3 years experience or Master’s Degree 1 years experience; 4 additional years experience in lieu of a degree is accepted.
Active Secret Security Clearance.
Candidates must be detailed oriented and have computer skills with working knowledge of SharePoint, CPLM and MS Office applications.
These Qualifications Would be Nice to Have:
Experience coordinating with IPTs on required deliverables.
CPLM knowledge of scheduling in support, planning and production.
Knowledge of and experience with configuration control and defect tracking systems.
Active Top Secret Security Clearance.
Current SAP/SAR accesses.
Work in a fast-paced environment with excellent written and oral communication skills.

Job Summary
Come join a vibrant data science research team in the emerging field of business lines product pricing and segmentation. A successful applicant is expected to be able to collaborate with business partners to develop predictive analytic solutions that enable data-driven strategic decision-making; and utilize data science techniques to manipulate large structured and unstructured data sets, identify patterns in raw data, and develop models to predict the likelihood of a future outcome and/or to optimize business solutions. This level reflects solid knowledge of predictive analytics techniques, while continuing to learn how to apply techniques to business issues.
Job Responsibilities
Apply knowledge of sophisticated analytics techniques to manipulate structured and unstructured datasets in order to generate insights to inform business decisions.
Identify and tests hypotheses, ensuring statistical significance, as part of building and developing predictive models for business application.
Translate quantitative analyses and findings into accessible visuals for non-technical audiences, providing a clear view into interpreting the data.
Enable the business to make clear trade-offs between and among choices, with a reasonable view into likely outcomes.
Create ML tools that support product pricing.
Be responsible for smaller components of projects of moderate-to-high complexity.
Regularly engage with the data science community and participates in cross-functional working groups.
The actual internal level/grade for this role will depend on the candidate's overall experience and skill level
Solid knowledge of predictive analytics techniques and statistical diagnostics of models.
Experienced and skilled in programming, preferred in Python.
Insurance industry experience is an advantage.
ML/NLP/Deep Learning knowledge/experience is an advantage.
Competencies for Analyst I, Data Science, typically acquired through a Master`s degree (in Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Actuarial Science or other scientific field of study) and 0-1 years of experience or may be acquired through a Bachelor`s degree and 3+ years of relevant experience.

Job Description
As an integral part of our Digital Analytics team, the Data Analyst is responsible for collecting, analyzing and presenting data to improve decision making around customer experience projects in Nordstrom’s high-growth Direct online channel. This individual should have a high degree of curiosity about the business and the skills to discover impactful insights from data. They should be able to communicate those insights in a way that builds confidence and enables decisions that drive business value.
A day in the life…
Partner with key stakeholders on data analysis problems
Mine complex digital behavioral data and transform it into actionable information
Apply common statistical methods, data modeling, and predictive analysis to answer strategic questions for the online business
Use advanced data visualization techniques to communicate solutions to business stakeholders
Provide exceptional customer service through professionalism, ownership and initiative
Demonstrate productivity through the efficient use of time and a commitment to strong results
You own this if you have…
A quantitative degree in mathematics, statistics, computer science, engineering, or similar quantitative analytics discipline
1+ years of corporate data analysis experience in online analytics (online retail a plus)
Strong experience with SQL
Familiarity with an analytic scripting language such as R or Python preferred
Good verbal and written communication skills, ability to convey results to non-experts
We’ve got you covered…

At COMHAR, it's our mission to provide health and human services that empower individuals, families and communities to live healthier, self-determined lives. We are currently expanding our CCBHC services and are looking for a Data Analyst to join our team.
DATA ANAYLST JOB DUTIES
The full-time Data Specialist is responsible for entering and maintaining grant data information and records.

Advanced skills in Microsoft Excel

Ally and Your Career
Ally Financial only succeeds when its people do - and that’s more than some cliché people put on job postings. We live this stuff! We see our people as, well, people - with interests, families, friends, dreams, and causes that are all important to them. Our focus is on the health and safety of our teammates as well as work-life balance and diversity and inclusion. From generous benefits to a variety of employee resource groups, we strive to build paths that encourage employees to stretch themselves professionally. We want to help you grow, develop, and learn new things. You’re constantly evolving, so shouldn’t your opportunities be, too?
The Opportunity
Reporting to the Director or Manager, the Treasury Analyst II is responsible for supporting Treasury and associated business partners throughout the organization. The Treasury Analyst II is responsible for routine activities, within aligned function, using existing procedures and policy. The Analyst performs day to day structured work assignments requiring only moderate instruction and guidance from more senior level roles.
The Work Itself
Core Responsibilities including applying sound technical knowledge (specific responsibilities will vary depending on the aligned functions/area):
Net Financing revenue forecasting, reporting and analysis.
Short term and long term liquidity forecasting.
Capital forecasting and analysis.
Trade execution and settlement.
Cash and liquid investments portfolio management.
Asset and liability hedging.
Funding strategy and execution.
Economic forecasting and analysis.
Applies relevant regulations, policies and procedures to business issues and day to day responsibilities.
The Skills You Bring
1+ years progressive experience in aligned area/functions (Structured Funding, Funding - Liquidity, Liquidity Risk, Treasury Operations, Capital and Balance Sheet Management, Capital Markets, Economics) in the financial industry.
Bachelor's degree in finance, accounting or economics preferred.
Building solid technical expertise, business and industry knowledge, and process and leadership capabilities.
Developing project management, analytical and judgment skills.
Developing ability to influence others and build consensus.
Ability to communicate effectively Increasing ability to work with limited supervision while applying previous experience to execute moderately complex tasks.
Ability to analyze possible solutions using standard procedures.
Increased technical skill using models and other forecasting tools.
Exhibit a strong work ethic and high degree of self-motivation.
Comfortable interacting with other personnel in group or support staff from other departments; may interact with other internal and external personnel (i.e., external auditors, regulators) on specific projects or routine matters, usually under supervision.
Advanced MS Excel (pivot tables, v-lookups, etc.).
How We'll Have Your Back
Ally's compensation program offers market-competitive base pay and pay-for-performance incentives (bonuses) based on achieving personal and company goals. But Ally’s total compensation – or total rewards – extends beyond your paycheck and is designed to support and enrich your personal and professional life, including:
Time Away: competitive holiday and flexible paid-time-off, including time off for volunteering and voting.
Planning for the Future: plan for the near and long term with an industry-leading 401K retirement savings plan with matching and company contributions, student loan and 529 educational assistance programs, tuition reimbursement, and other financial well-being programs.
Supporting your Health & Well-being: flexible health and insurance options including dental and vision, pre-tax Health Savings Account with employer contributions and a total well-being program that helps you and your family stay on track physically, socially, emotionally, and financially.
Building a Family: adoption, surrogacy, and fertility support as well as parental and caregiver leave, back-up child and adult/elder day care program and childcare discounts.
Work-Life Integration: other benefits including LifeMatters® Employee Assistance Program, subsidized and discounted Weight Watchers® program and other employee discount programs.
Who We Are:
Ally Financial is a customer-centric, leading digital financial services company with passionate customer service and innovative financial solutions. We are relentlessly focused on "Doing it Right" and being a trusted financial-services provider to our consumer, commercial, and corporate customers. For more information, visit www.ally.com.
Ally is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, race, color, sex, religion, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, pregnancy status, marital status, military or veteran status, genetic disposition or any other reason protected by law.

We are committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodation to applicants with physical or mental disabilities. For accommodation requests, email us at work@ally.com.
